race.comment: Small field but some very capable types lining up here. STIRRUP CUP (4) is Stakes-placed at his best and has been tackling some stronger races this this over the spring. He will concede a start but if he's within a few lengths at the top of the straight, he can win. NASHO (3) is on the quick back-up after running well last Saturday. He draws well, will roll forward with the claim and will take some catching. HARD PRINCE (5) might be ready to win. He caught the eye when getting home from near-last at his most recent start. He might be able to settle closer form the low draw here. DUAL PRESSURE (2) hasn't done much wrong this preparation and looks an each-way chance again, while KOMACHI (6) maps to get the perfect run and can finish in the money.
